³MARY LOUISE LEATHERS
Died 12 Dec 1992 (aged 79)
"Secretary at the famous Coleman's Mustard Company
and fondly remembered as a crafty card player"
A much loved Great Aunt, Aunt and Sister

THELMA GERTRUDE LEATHERS
Died 5 Nov 1990 (aged 88)
'The speediest ambulance driver in WW2, with her bright smile
and a G&T in hand playing the fruit machines.'
A much loved Great Aunt, Aunt and Sister

EVELYN JOAN KIDNER
(formerly Leathers)
16 Nov 1914 - 28 July 2002 (aged 87)
'The best grandmother in the world, a brilliant artist
and lovingly remembered for her delicious afternoon teas'
